SIMPLE: nighthawk
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nighthawk
<hw>nighthawk</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A person who likes to
be active late at night; a <altname>night owl</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> night owl, nightbird.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any of several mainly nocturnal
North American goatsuckers, especially <spn>Chordeiles minor</spn>, or
the related European goatsucker <spn>Caprimulgus europaeus</spn>, also
called the nightjar.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bullbat, mosquito hawk.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nightie</ent>⟦br⟧
